Rev Tamas wrote:

&gt; Thanks!
&gt; So I need to use not the API but the command-line interface.

I&#39;d suggest following Yan&#39;s suggestion and get the command line 
interface working first.  Once thats working against your ARCs and its 
not throwing &#39;Failed to find GZIP MAGIC&#39; complaints, then move to using 
the ARCReader API. Study how the ARCReader#main works for example usage 
of the ARCReader API (Pass the &#39;--help&#39; to see ARCReader options).

The &#39;Failed to find GZIP MAGIC&#39; message means ARCReader is failing to 
parse the ARC: Its trying to find the next gzip member in what it thinks 
a gzipped stream and is unable to find the MAGIC number that introduces 
the gzip header.  Test your ARCs with &#39;gzip -t&#39; to see that they are 
wholesome gzip files before giving them to ARCReader.

